12/12/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Education and Science Minister Slobodan Backovic and Macedonian counterpart Azis Polozani sealed a bilateral agreement on co-operation in the field of science, technology and education Friday (9 December). They also vowed increased exchange and communication between the Macedonian and Montenegrin academies of science and higher educational institutions. Polozani is expected to sign a similar agreement during a visit to Tirana on Monday. (Makfax - 11/12/05; Macedonian Government Web site - 09/12/05)
